WEBVTT

1
00:00:09.137 --> 00:00:12.241
- [Narrator] Colonel William
Guile. one of the greatest

2
00:00:12.241 --> 00:00:14.413
martial artists in the world
travels the global tournament

3
00:00:14.413 --> 00:00:17.655
circuit. using it to conceal
his top secret mission

4
00:00:17.655 --> 00:00:21.241
as leader of an elite group of
international crime fighters

5
00:00:21.241 --> 00:00:24.620
known only by their code
name. Street Fighter.

6
00:00:25.689 --> 00:00:29.827
The heroic man beast. Blanka.

7
00:00:29.827 --> 00:00:33.000
Hard kicking fighting
machine. Chun-Li.

8
00:00:34.103 --> 00:00:36.758
[intense music]

9
00:00:40.034 --> 00:00:43.206
And a team of the most
amazing warriors ever seen

10
00:00:43.206 --> 00:00:46.689
have joined forces with Guile
to combat the criminal empire

11
00:00:46.689 --> 00:00:50.517
of Shadaloo and its super
human leader. Bison.

12
00:00:50.517 --> 00:00:52.379
They have their
own code of honor.

13
00:00:52.379 --> 00:00:55.827
Discipline. justice. commitment.

14
00:00:55.827 --> 00:01:00.103
And together they will triumph
against the forces of evil.

15
00:01:05.758 --> 00:01:07.000
Street Fighter!

16
00:01:08.689 --> 00:01:11.344
[ominous music]

17
00:01:16.482 --> 00:01:20.344
- [Announcer] Welcome for our
own local freestyle champion.

18
00:01:20.344 --> 00:01:22.000
the Crimson Crawdad!

19
00:01:24.275 --> 00:01:27.448
[crowd cheering]

20
00:01:27.448 --> 00:01:29.137
And in this corner
is challenger.

21
00:01:29.137 --> 00:01:32.931
the man who put the chicken
into chicken colonel.

22
00:01:32.931 --> 00:01:36.068
the golden ego.
Colonel William Guile.

23
00:01:37.000 --> 00:01:38.206
[grunting]

24
00:01:38.206 --> 00:01:40.275
- Come on. come on big shot.

25
00:01:40.275 --> 00:01:41.724
[grunting]

26
00:01:41.724 --> 00:01:44.310
I hear you used to be somebody.

27
00:01:44.310 --> 00:01:46.586
- That's right.
punk. I used to be.

28
00:01:48.241 --> 00:01:49.068
- Pincer grip!

29
00:01:51.344 --> 00:01:52.413
- Traitor. deserter!

30
00:01:57.034 --> 00:02:00.206
- Now why'd you have
to go and do that?

31
00:02:04.586 --> 00:02:05.931
- Coward!

32
00:02:05.931 --> 00:02:08.586
[loud thudding]

33
00:02:10.896 --> 00:02:13.586
- [Crimson Crawdad] On TV it
said when you were in Shadaloo

34
00:02:13.586 --> 00:02:15.793
with the international
peace keeping forces.

35
00:02:15.793 --> 00:02:18.896
you ran out on your own troops.

36
00:02:18.896 --> 00:02:20.034
[yelling]

37
00:02:20.034 --> 00:02:22.275
- Sonic boom!

38
00:02:22.275 --> 00:02:24.965
[loud thudding]

39
00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:28.827
- Don't believe
everything you hear.

40
00:02:30.034 --> 00:02:32.724
[ominous music]

41
00:02:44.413 --> 00:02:45.793
You wanted me. sir?

42
00:02:45.793 --> 00:02:47.620
- [Escher] I hear
you weren't very

43
00:02:47.620 --> 00:02:48.896
popular down at
that club. Colonel.

44
00:02:48.896 --> 00:02:50.344
How are you holding up?

45
00:02:50.344 --> 00:02:53.517
- Well playing a lowlife
isn't my idea of a good time.

46
00:02:53.517 --> 00:02:55.724
- We both know your deep
cover story is vital

47
00:02:55.724 --> 00:02:57.758
to the entire Street
Fighter operation.

48
00:02:57.758 --> 00:02:59.275
The world needs us again.

49
00:02:59.275 --> 00:03:03.310
It's a little more complicated
than your usual assignment.

50
00:03:03.310 --> 00:03:06.655
No high tech bombs to diffuse.
no terrorist army to stop.

51
00:03:06.655 --> 00:03:10.517
This time your enemy is a virus.

52
00:03:10.517 --> 00:03:12.034
- I hate colds.

53
00:03:12.034 --> 00:03:14.724
I take it this is worse?

54
00:03:14.724 --> 00:03:16.206
- It'll take you out in a day.

55
00:03:18.068 --> 00:03:20.724
It could wipe out
the planet in a week.

56
00:03:20.724 --> 00:03:23.586
Special operations sent in a
team of doctors to contain it.

57
00:03:23.586 --> 00:03:24.965
but they're missing.

58
00:03:24.965 --> 00:03:25.793
- Sick?

59
00:03:25.793 --> 00:03:27.103
- Kidnapped.

60
00:03:27.103 --> 00:03:29.241
We need you to assemble
a street fighter team.

61
00:03:29.241 --> 00:03:32.620
Find the medics. find out
who took them. and why.

62
00:03:32.620 --> 00:03:34.793
- And not get the
sniffles doing it.

63
00:03:34.793 --> 00:03:36.137
- Right.

64
00:03:36.137 --> 00:03:39.586
Guile. the public
can't know about this.

65
00:03:39.586 --> 00:03:42.103
It must be a Street
Fighter operation.

66
00:03:42.103 --> 00:03:43.862
At whatever cost to
you and your team.

67
00:03:43.862 --> 00:03:47.310
the virus must not
be allowed to spread.

68
00:03:47.310 --> 00:03:49.379
- So what do I do when
I find this virus.

69
00:03:49.379 --> 00:03:51.724
give it plenty of liquids
and put it to bed?

70
00:03:51.724 --> 00:03:53.275
- That's up to the medical team.

71
00:03:53.275 --> 00:03:56.034
This is our last
contact with them.

72
00:03:56.034 --> 00:03:57.586
A phone relay to
our security base

73
00:03:57.586 --> 00:03:59.482
in San Paulo about
either hours ago.

74
00:03:59.482 --> 00:04:01.379
I think you'll have
some personal interest.

75
00:04:01.379 --> 00:04:02.931
- [Cindy] We are under attack.

76
00:04:02.931 --> 00:04:04.413
Repeat. we are...

77
00:04:06.586 --> 00:04:08.551
- We'll issue whatever
fire power you want.

78
00:04:08.551 --> 00:04:11.448
- You know I hate guns.
guns are for wimps.

79
00:04:11.448 --> 00:04:12.758
- Alright.

80
00:04:12.758 --> 00:04:13.931
But the clock's ticking. Guile.

81
00:04:13.931 --> 00:04:16.241
no time to assemble
the full team.

82
00:04:16.241 --> 00:04:19.034
- Well. let's see what other
operatives we have in the area.

83
00:04:19.034 --> 00:04:20.034
- [Escher] Chun-Li.

84
00:04:20.034 --> 00:04:21.310
- [Guile] Good.

85
00:04:21.310 --> 00:04:22.241
- [Escher] Though
there are a couple

86
00:04:22.241 --> 00:04:24.103
of freelancers in the area.

87
00:04:24.103 --> 00:04:25.793
- Not them.

88
00:04:25.793 --> 00:04:27.206
- [Escher] Good luck. Colonel.

89
00:04:27.206 --> 00:04:30.068
- With Ken and Ryu.
thanks. I'm gonna need it.

90
00:04:32.275 --> 00:04:35.034
[birds chirping]

91
00:04:36.068 --> 00:04:38.206
- Diamonds. rubies. aw man

92
00:04:38.206 --> 00:04:40.689
the Temple of Lost
Treasure awaits.

93
00:04:40.689 --> 00:04:42.655
- It wouldn't be waiting if some

94
00:04:42.655 --> 00:04:44.827
bonehead hadn't lost the map.

95
00:04:44.827 --> 00:04:48.034
- Well lucky for you I've
got a photographic memory.

96
00:04:48.034 --> 00:04:53.034
That temple's right over.
over there someplace.

97
00:04:54.241 --> 00:04:55.931
- That's what you
said two days ago.

98
00:04:55.931 --> 00:04:57.448
[loud thudding]

99
00:04:57.448 --> 00:05:01.586
- Ryu. are you. are you okay?

100
00:05:01.586 --> 00:05:03.482
[coughing]

101
00:05:03.482 --> 00:05:06.517
- Aw man. I've been
slimmed by Arnold the pig.

102
00:05:06.517 --> 00:05:09.310
Okay that's it. I'm outta here.

103
00:05:09.310 --> 00:05:11.896
- But what about
all that treasure?

104
00:05:11.896 --> 00:05:14.655
Cars. boats. babes.

105
00:05:14.655 --> 00:05:16.482
Come on man. just one more day.

106
00:05:16.482 --> 00:05:20.310
If we don't find that
temple today. we head home.

107
00:05:20.310 --> 00:05:23.586
- One day. sundown.
temple or no temple.

108
00:05:26.241 --> 00:05:30.172
[speaking in foreign language]

109
00:05:31.103 --> 00:05:32.586
Colonel Guile.

110
00:05:32.586 --> 00:05:33.413
- What are you doing here?

111
00:05:33.413 --> 00:05:34.344
- Meeting a friend.

112
00:05:34.344 --> 00:05:37.068
Ah ah ah. these are for my team.

113
00:05:37.068 --> 00:05:41.413
- Uh. you uh. need
some more players?

114
00:05:43.000 --> 00:05:43.862
[sighing]

115
00:05:43.862 --> 00:05:45.482
- I'm gonna regret this.

116
00:05:51.068 --> 00:05:53.482
- It's okay. I'll
handle the rest myself.

117
00:05:55.758 --> 00:05:58.068
- [Man] Give us your money.

118
00:05:58.068 --> 00:06:00.034
- I didn't hear the magic word.

119
00:06:00.034 --> 00:06:03.103
[intense rock music]

120
00:06:04.310 --> 00:06:06.551
[grunting]

121
00:06:12.068 --> 00:06:14.862
[loud splashing]

122
00:06:17.896 --> 00:06:20.482
[air swooshing rapidly]

123
00:06:20.482 --> 00:06:22.758
[yelling]

124
00:06:22.758 --> 00:06:24.413
- Good morning Chun-Li.

125
00:06:24.413 --> 00:06:25.931
What took you so long?

126
00:06:25.931 --> 00:06:27.862
- I had a little
trouble with my bags.

127
00:06:32.931 --> 00:06:34.379
- Not much to go on Colonel.

128
00:06:34.379 --> 00:06:36.862
No trails out of
here that I can see.

129
00:06:36.862 --> 00:06:37.689
- Keep looking.

130
00:06:38.793 --> 00:06:41.896
- So. when do we
ditch for the temple?

131
00:06:41.896 --> 00:06:44.206
- Discipline.
justice. commitment.

132
00:06:44.206 --> 00:06:46.275
You forget the Street
Fighter code of honor?

133
00:06:46.275 --> 00:06:48.827
- We have done the code already.

134
00:06:48.827 --> 00:06:50.379
- For an hour.

135
00:06:51.551 --> 00:06:52.931
- Cross your fingers.

136
00:06:52.931 --> 00:06:55.137
I found a surveillance
unit that didn't melt.

137
00:06:56.931 --> 00:06:59.379
- This is Dr. Davila.
Operation Amber.

138
00:06:59.379 --> 00:07:02.275
This is a mayday.
we have a mayday.

139
00:07:02.275 --> 00:07:04.068
We are under attack.

140
00:07:04.068 --> 00:07:05.793
Repeat. we are...

141
00:07:05.793 --> 00:07:07.655
- Hear that?

142
00:07:07.655 --> 00:07:10.413
Sounds like high
frequency masa-rays.

143
00:07:10.413 --> 00:07:12.896
Whoever captured the medics
wanted them to function.

144
00:07:12.896 --> 00:07:15.896
But they'll have hefty
headaches when they come to.

145
00:07:15.896 --> 00:07:16.793
[grunting]

146
00:07:16.793 --> 00:07:17.758
You know her?

147
00:07:17.758 --> 00:07:18.931
A little personal history?

148
00:07:18.931 --> 00:07:22.000
- A lot. in my old life.

149
00:07:22.000 --> 00:07:24.482
- Sorry. Guile. I didn't know.

150
00:07:24.482 --> 00:07:26.344
- Hey. you weren't supposed to.

151
00:07:26.344 --> 00:07:27.275
Come on.

152
00:07:27.275 --> 00:07:28.586
- She must be something special.

153
00:07:30.689 --> 00:07:32.137
- Those scrapes on the branches

154
00:07:32.137 --> 00:07:35.344
indicate military hovercraft.
and more than one.

155
00:07:35.344 --> 00:07:38.000
- Where'd they get 'em.
village Rent A Tank?

156
00:07:38.000 --> 00:07:40.241
- This wasn't done by locals.

157
00:07:40.241 --> 00:07:41.931
It's Bison.

158
00:07:41.931 --> 00:07:44.000
- [Chung-Li Voiceover] The
man who killed my father.

159
00:07:44.000 --> 00:07:45.344
Father's spirit will never rest

160
00:07:45.344 --> 00:07:47.586
until Bison pays for his crimes.

161
00:07:53.000 --> 00:07:55.758
[group chanting]

162
00:08:09.655 --> 00:08:12.310
[loud growling]

163
00:08:30.724 --> 00:08:33.034
- Welcome. welcome. welcome.

164
00:08:34.241 --> 00:08:38.000
so good of you to
accept my invitation.

165
00:08:38.000 --> 00:08:42.965
I am Bison. and I am most
curious about your work.

166
00:08:42.965 --> 00:08:45.310
- What do you know
about our work?

167
00:08:45.310 --> 00:08:47.724
- I know your Operation
Amber has been looking

168
00:08:47.724 --> 00:08:51.310
for a cure for a virus so
deadly that it could wipe out

169
00:08:51.310 --> 00:08:55.172
every living human were
to escape this dark place.

170
00:08:55.172 --> 00:08:57.551
- Then why did you
disrupt our work?

171
00:08:57.551 --> 00:08:59.586
- Because you weren't
working fast enough.

172
00:08:59.586 --> 00:09:01.896
This virus simply
hadn't infected

173
00:09:01.896 --> 00:09:04.413
enough people for you to study.

174
00:09:04.413 --> 00:09:07.275
Oh yes. a few boars.
a few monkeys.

175
00:09:07.275 --> 00:09:11.000
but you just didn't have the
tools you need to succeed.

176
00:09:11.000 --> 00:09:12.275
- Tools?

177
00:09:12.275 --> 00:09:13.793
- People.

178
00:09:13.793 --> 00:09:18.551
You need a pool of people
to examine. to work on.

179
00:09:19.413 --> 00:09:20.620
- This virus is terminal.

180
00:09:20.620 --> 00:09:23.172
We're close but we
still don't have a cure.

181
00:09:23.172 --> 00:09:25.931
Infecting innocent people
is not going to change that.

182
00:09:25.931 --> 00:09:28.241
- Oh but I think it will.

183
00:09:28.241 --> 00:09:31.724
Necessity is the mother of
invention. and all that.

184
00:09:31.724 --> 00:09:34.379
In 12 hours at sunrise
the hatch will open.

185
00:09:34.379 --> 00:09:37.137
the balloon containing
the virus will explode.

186
00:09:37.137 --> 00:09:39.793
it's contents will coat
everything in the room.

187
00:09:40.655 --> 00:09:42.517
You may escort our latest guests

188
00:09:42.517 --> 00:09:45.724
into their accommodations now.

189
00:09:45.724 --> 00:09:48.827
Your friends receiving
direct physical contact

190
00:09:48.827 --> 00:09:52.034
with the viral agents.
will become infected and.

191
00:09:52.034 --> 00:09:54.103
- No. stop it.

192
00:09:54.103 --> 00:09:56.413
- It's up to you to save them.

193
00:09:56.413 --> 00:09:58.689
And when you've succeeded.
you let me know.

194
00:10:00.000 --> 00:10:01.862
- Looks like there was
some kind of struggle.

195
00:10:01.862 --> 00:10:05.172
But whoever was here. is gone.

196
00:10:05.172 --> 00:10:06.000
- Guile!

197
00:10:06.000 --> 00:10:08.275
[grunting]

198
00:10:09.482 --> 00:10:11.379
- [Blanka] What have
you done with them?

199
00:10:11.379 --> 00:10:14.068
[screaming]

200
00:10:14.068 --> 00:10:16.344
[growling]

201
00:10:18.448 --> 00:10:20.275
- Sonic boom!

202
00:10:20.275 --> 00:10:22.000
[loud thudding]

203
00:10:22.000 --> 00:10:25.000
Okay jungle boy. let's.

204
00:10:25.000 --> 00:10:25.862
Blanka?

205
00:10:28.034 --> 00:10:29.551
- Guile.

206
00:10:29.551 --> 00:10:32.172
What are you doing here?

207
00:10:32.172 --> 00:10:34.655
And what have you
done with my brothers?

208
00:10:34.655 --> 00:10:36.068
- Your brothers?

209
00:10:36.068 --> 00:10:37.379
- Blanka?

210
00:10:37.379 --> 00:10:39.689
Aren't you supposed to
be dead or something.

211
00:10:39.689 --> 00:10:41.172
[growling]

212
00:10:41.172 --> 00:10:43.758
- Blanka. it's just that we're
all surprised to see you.

213
00:10:43.758 --> 00:10:48.724
- After Bison turned me
into this. this thing.

214
00:10:50.172 --> 00:10:53.689
I came here so no one would
ever have to look at me again.

215
00:10:53.689 --> 00:10:55.068
I can't be with people.

216
00:10:56.034 --> 00:10:57.000
I get angry.

217
00:10:58.448 --> 00:11:01.000
- Then who are these brothers
you were talking about?

218
00:11:02.137 --> 00:11:04.241
- The Inca mystics
of the temple.

219
00:11:04.241 --> 00:11:08.206
I lived like an animal
in the rainforest.

220
00:11:08.206 --> 00:11:12.517
until they found
me and healed me.

221
00:11:13.482 --> 00:11:15.448
- Did he say temple?

222
00:11:15.448 --> 00:11:19.793
- They've lived here for
1.000 years. peaceful. wise.

223
00:11:21.034 --> 00:11:23.724
They had left for meditations
when I heard them.

224
00:11:23.724 --> 00:11:26.896
and now they're gone.
and you're here.

225
00:11:26.896 --> 00:11:28.758
Where are they!?

226
00:11:28.758 --> 00:11:31.862
- I don't know. Blanka. but
I think I know who took them.

227
00:11:31.862 --> 00:11:33.068
It's Bison.

228
00:11:33.068 --> 00:11:35.517
- But. he can't be alive.

229
00:11:35.517 --> 00:11:38.137
It's impossible.

230
00:11:38.137 --> 00:11:40.896
- Come with us. Blanka.
we'll fight Bison together.

231
00:11:40.896 --> 00:11:42.758
It'll be like old times.

232
00:11:42.758 --> 00:11:44.896
- I'll fight with you. Guile.

233
00:11:44.896 --> 00:11:48.068
this one time until
my brothers are safe.

234
00:11:50.413 --> 00:11:53.034
- [Bison] Well Doctor.
how goes the good fight?

235
00:11:53.034 --> 00:11:54.482
- Get away from me. Bison.

236
00:11:54.482 --> 00:11:56.413
Every second you
distract me cuts

237
00:11:56.413 --> 00:11:58.931
the chances for
saving these people.

238
00:11:58.931 --> 00:12:00.827
- I take it then that
you're closing in

239
00:12:00.827 --> 00:12:03.793
on a vaccine for my volunteers?

240
00:12:03.793 --> 00:12:05.482
- We're close to a treatment.

241
00:12:05.482 --> 00:12:06.793
Now go away!

242
00:12:08.448 --> 00:12:10.137
- Ken. Ryu?

243
00:12:11.241 --> 00:12:12.482
- What is it?

244
00:12:12.482 --> 00:12:14.896
- Ken and Ryu are gone.

245
00:12:14.896 --> 00:12:17.482
- Hmm. they lasted
longer than I thought.

246
00:12:17.482 --> 00:12:18.689
Come on.

247
00:12:18.689 --> 00:12:19.931
- Then why'd you
bother bringing them

248
00:12:19.931 --> 00:12:21.758
on this mission in
the first place?

249
00:12:21.758 --> 00:12:24.103
- Because they could
be the best if they'd

250
00:12:24.103 --> 00:12:27.137
quit flaking off for a
minute and concentrate.

251
00:12:27.137 --> 00:12:29.586
Discipline. justice. commitment.

252
00:12:29.586 --> 00:12:32.310
Ken thinks it just means
less time to party.

253
00:12:32.310 --> 00:12:34.827
Besides. I thought
you liked them.

254
00:12:36.862 --> 00:12:40.000
- [Ken] So. now
do you believe me?

255
00:12:40.000 --> 00:12:43.275
- I'm uh. still not
sure we should be here.

256
00:12:43.275 --> 00:12:46.103
- Oh come to papa.

257
00:12:46.103 --> 00:12:47.862
- It's not right. Ken.

258
00:12:47.862 --> 00:12:49.517
These things don't belong to us.

259
00:12:49.517 --> 00:12:51.689
What about our code. huh?

260
00:12:51.689 --> 00:12:54.965
- Wake up and smell
the silver polish. man.

261
00:12:54.965 --> 00:12:56.793
If Bison's got
Blanka's brothers.

262
00:12:56.793 --> 00:12:58.896
they won't be needing
this stuff anymore.

263
00:12:58.896 --> 00:12:59.655
Am I right?

264
00:13:00.758 --> 00:13:03.310
- Ken. we don't.

265
00:13:03.310 --> 00:13:04.413
[loud thudding]

266
00:13:04.413 --> 00:13:05.241
- Ryu!

267
00:13:10.862 --> 00:13:13.517
[intense music]

268
00:13:19.586 --> 00:13:20.413
- Stop.

269
00:13:22.172 --> 00:13:24.448
[groaning]

270
00:13:25.965 --> 00:13:28.931
- Uh uh uh. guns are a no no.

271
00:13:28.931 --> 00:13:29.758
- No!

272
00:13:30.793 --> 00:13:33.448
[alarm blaring]

273
00:13:34.413 --> 00:13:36.310
- I hate when that happens.

274
00:13:37.793 --> 00:13:38.689
Sonic boom!

275
00:13:40.965 --> 00:13:43.172
[groaning]

276
00:13:49.068 --> 00:13:52.241
[electricity zapping]

277
00:13:55.310 --> 00:13:58.413
[glass shattering]

278
00:13:58.413 --> 00:13:59.689
- What's going on out there?

279
00:13:59.689 --> 00:14:02.379
Come. you may prove useful yet.

280
00:14:04.551 --> 00:14:07.724
- [Chun-Li] Cavalry's
here. everybody out.

281
00:14:14.655 --> 00:14:17.000
- No sign of our guests yet.

282
00:14:17.000 --> 00:14:18.275
- What are you doing?

283
00:14:18.275 --> 00:14:19.689
- [Bison] Terminating
the experiment.

284
00:14:19.689 --> 00:14:22.758
[explosions booming]

285
00:14:26.827 --> 00:14:28.862
- The supplies. stop it!

286
00:14:28.862 --> 00:14:30.241
- [Blanka] Bison!

287
00:14:31.379 --> 00:14:35.137
- Why Blanka. is that you?

288
00:14:35.137 --> 00:14:38.551
I was sick to think I'd
lost you at Shadaloo.

289
00:14:39.413 --> 00:14:41.655
[growling]

290
00:14:43.068 --> 00:14:45.310
[grunting]

291
00:14:49.758 --> 00:14:50.586
- Demon!

292
00:14:53.379 --> 00:14:56.413
[grunting]

293
00:14:56.413 --> 00:14:59.862
- Your ingratitude
leaves me no choice.

294
00:14:59.862 --> 00:15:03.379
Your friends had over
11 hours left to live.

295
00:15:03.379 --> 00:15:05.034
My how time flies.

296
00:15:06.000 --> 00:15:06.896
- The virus.

297
00:15:10.034 --> 00:15:12.103
[grunting]

298
00:15:12.103 --> 00:15:14.517
- Quickly. get out of here.

299
00:15:14.517 --> 00:15:17.172
[timer beeping]

300
00:15:19.000 --> 00:15:21.206
[growling]

301
00:15:21.206 --> 00:15:22.241
- No!

302
00:15:22.241 --> 00:15:25.172
- Cindy. Cindy. are you alright?

303
00:15:25.172 --> 00:15:26.689
- William?

304
00:15:26.689 --> 00:15:28.000
Why are you here?

305
00:15:28.000 --> 00:15:30.344
Do you work for
this Bison creature?

306
00:15:30.344 --> 00:15:32.068
- Whatever you may
think of me. Cindy.

307
00:15:32.068 --> 00:15:34.206
I haven't fallen that low.

308
00:15:34.206 --> 00:15:36.275
- The old William
Guile never would have.

309
00:15:37.137 --> 00:15:38.551
But since the court marshal.

310
00:15:38.551 --> 00:15:41.172
I feel like I don't
know you anymore.

311
00:15:41.172 --> 00:15:42.724
Why are you here?

312
00:15:42.724 --> 00:15:43.793
- I can't tell you.

313
00:15:43.793 --> 00:15:45.586
I want to. but I can't.

314
00:15:45.586 --> 00:15:48.310
- We used to trust
each other. William.

315
00:15:48.310 --> 00:15:50.344
I used to think I
meant something to you.

316
00:15:56.275 --> 00:15:57.206
- You still do.

317
00:15:58.379 --> 00:16:01.620
[loud thudding]

318
00:16:01.620 --> 00:16:03.000
- Blanka.

319
00:16:03.000 --> 00:16:04.931
- Careful. he's been exposed.

320
00:16:04.931 --> 00:16:06.482
I don't know if I can help him.

321
00:16:09.034 --> 00:16:09.896
- Bison!

322
00:16:11.862 --> 00:16:14.000
- [Bison] He who
fights then runs away.

323
00:16:14.000 --> 00:16:15.965
- [Guile] Is a cowardly scum.

324
00:16:15.965 --> 00:16:17.862
- Guile!

325
00:16:17.862 --> 00:16:21.482
Normally I wouldn't miss a
chance to fight you. Colonel.

326
00:16:21.482 --> 00:16:22.551
Magnetic pulse!

327
00:16:27.758 --> 00:16:30.172
[groaning]

328
00:16:30.172 --> 00:16:33.758
But something in the night
air soon won't agree with me.

329
00:16:39.896 --> 00:16:41.206
- [Cindy] William. no!

330
00:16:48.172 --> 00:16:49.965
- That meddling fool.

331
00:16:52.655 --> 00:16:54.517
Happy landing.

332
00:16:54.517 --> 00:16:55.758
Magnetic pulse!

333
00:16:56.793 --> 00:17:00.172
[electricity zapping]

334
00:17:00.172 --> 00:17:02.413
[grunting]

335
00:17:03.620 --> 00:17:05.793
[yelling]

336
00:17:11.517 --> 00:17:13.896
[loud thudding]

337
00:17:13.896 --> 00:17:15.517
- Ken.

338
00:17:15.517 --> 00:17:17.689
What's wrong. scam
didn't pan out?

339
00:17:17.689 --> 00:17:20.827
- Colonel. I mean
Guile. Ryu reminded me

340
00:17:20.827 --> 00:17:23.172
what our Street Fighter
code really stands for.

341
00:17:23.172 --> 00:17:26.206
Help him. please.
he's real sick.

342
00:17:30.000 --> 00:17:31.620
- [Cindy] I'm sorry. we can make

343
00:17:31.620 --> 00:17:33.206
him comfortable. but
that's about all.

344
00:17:33.206 --> 00:17:37.344
- Ah come on. man. you doctors
have a pill for everything.

345
00:17:37.344 --> 00:17:40.103
- Dr. Davila. come
quickly. it's Blanka.

346
00:17:40.103 --> 00:17:42.689
- Probably time to
say your goodbyes.

347
00:17:42.689 --> 00:17:44.689
I'm sorry. William.

348
00:17:44.689 --> 00:17:47.965
- I'm. I'm thirsty.

349
00:17:47.965 --> 00:17:49.655
- Should he be thirsty?

350
00:17:49.655 --> 00:17:52.724
- He shouldn't be alive.

351
00:17:53.827 --> 00:17:56.034
I don't believe it. this is it.

352
00:17:56.034 --> 00:17:58.827
Whatever Bison did to
Blanka to transform him

353
00:17:58.827 --> 00:18:02.275
into this. has altered
his immune system.

354
00:18:02.275 --> 00:18:05.241
He's producing anti-bodies
that are fighting the virus.

355
00:18:05.241 --> 00:18:06.793
Don't you understand?

356
00:18:06.793 --> 00:18:10.586
His blood can cure anyone who
gets sick from this. like Ryu.

357
00:18:10.586 --> 00:18:12.689
It can be the basis
for a vaccine.

358
00:18:16.000 --> 00:18:18.344
- The Street Fighters
need you. friend.

359
00:18:18.344 --> 00:18:19.827
I need you.

360
00:18:19.827 --> 00:18:23.275
We work in secret. no
glory but no interference.

361
00:18:23.275 --> 00:18:25.413
Discipline. justice. commitment.

362
00:18:25.413 --> 00:18:28.344
We make a difference.
think about it.

363
00:18:31.862 --> 00:18:33.620
- You realize you're
asking him to leave

364
00:18:33.620 --> 00:18:35.965
his life here where
he's found peace?

365
00:18:35.965 --> 00:18:38.413
You can't know what
that will cost him.

366
00:18:38.413 --> 00:18:41.000
giving up the one thing he
loves most in this life.

367
00:18:42.034 --> 00:18:44.793
[dramatic music]

368
00:18:54.689 --> 00:18:57.758
[helicopter engine buzzing]

369
00:18:57.758 --> 00:18:59.275
- I have some idea.

370
00:19:00.103 --> 00:19:02.275
- Hey Street Fighter.

371
00:19:02.275 --> 00:19:04.000
- I want to thank you. Blanka.

372
00:19:04.000 --> 00:19:07.000
- We wanna thank
you. all of you.

373
00:19:07.000 --> 00:19:09.103
for what you did for Ryu here.

374
00:19:09.103 --> 00:19:12.448
Now I'm stuck with this joker.

375
00:19:12.448 --> 00:19:14.103
Are you sure you
don't wanna hang out?

376
00:19:14.103 --> 00:19:17.827
I hear Tierra del Fuego's
got some killer waves.

377
00:19:17.827 --> 00:19:19.034
- Waves?

378
00:19:19.034 --> 00:19:21.068
Wait a minute. you
said there was work.

379
00:19:22.655 --> 00:19:23.482
- Guile?

380
00:19:23.482 --> 00:19:24.482
- Yeah pal.

381
00:19:24.482 --> 00:19:26.275
- For 10 years I
got into nothing

382
00:19:26.275 --> 00:19:28.344
but trouble hanging
around with you.

383
00:19:28.344 --> 00:19:31.379
Any sane person would
stay 1.000 miles away.

384
00:19:31.379 --> 00:19:33.448
Count me in.

385
00:19:33.448 --> 00:19:34.275
- Alright!

386
00:19:35.448 --> 00:19:39.689
- Now about that $30
bucks you owe me.

387
00:19:41.172 --> 00:19:42.758
- Oh wait a minute.

388
00:19:45.137 --> 00:19:47.758
[upbeat music]
